## 6. Design System Summary (for your team)

* **Colors**

  * Primary: `blue-600`, `blue-700`, `indigo-800`
  * Success: green (metrics, good performance)
  * Warning: yellow (pending, borderline)
  * Danger: red (poor performance, many transfers)
  * Background: `gray-50` page, white cards, `gray-100` nav strips
* **Typography**

  * Masthead title: uppercase, 4xl, bold, tracking-wide
  * Hero title: 3xlâ€“4xl, bold
  * Section titles: 2xl, bold
  * Story titles: `lg`â€“`xl`, semibold
  * Body: `text-base`, relaxed line-height
* **Components**

  * Cards: white, `rounded-xl`, shadow-sm, light border
  * Tables: zebra rows, row hover, clear column labels
  * Badges / Status pills: colour-coded (green/yellow/red)
  * Progress: could be used later (e.g., % answered, appeals)
* **Spacing**

  * Page padding: `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
  * Vertical gaps: `py-8` between big sections
  * Grid gaps: `gap-6` on desktop
  * Card padding: `p-5` or `p-6`
* **Responsiveness**

  * Mobile: single column, important cards first in logical narrative:
    Hero â†’ Your Area â†’ What People Are Asking â†’ Fresh Answers â†’ Latest Activity â†’ Departments â†’ Rights â†’ Toolkit â†’ others.
  * Tablet: 2 columns; some full-width blocks (Spotlight, Browse by Topic).
  * Desktop: full 3-column â€œnewspaperâ€ layout.
